@VentKazemaru This discussion by this point feels like petty bitching, honestly
Dark Souls was released ages ago, let it fucking rest

@VentKazemaru Saying that "oh but it is too hard and I have no ability" is honestly being lazy, because I know people that play like shit and eventually they managed to beat it
If you think the game being that hard gives you no joy in beating the bosses then again, not for you pal

@VentKazemaru I can genuinely understand the argument of "some people don't have the free time to go through it all in that level" then my say is like, "then the game isn't for you pal", better not to experience than to be completely underwhelmed with a lackluster experience overall

@VentKazemaru Dark Souls is always the example yeah, and I find it to be kinda bullshit. Dark Souls wants to give that exact experience of a vast, large and ruthless ambient iN which survival is hard and the journey is to overcome hardships
An easy mode on that would just go against the idea

People need to stop thinking that every game is supposed to be played by everyone, and also stop to think that "mmm...maybe this is the dev's ideal and forcing him to do something he doesn't want may ruin the experience of both creating it and playing it on any setting"

@VentKazemaru I kind of agree, honestly I am of the opinion that if the game is meant to give a certain experience, forcing someone to change it to access someone who wouldn't be interested in the game otherwise is kind of a waste of time
It is just a matter of "this game isn't for you then"->
